---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="LuminNote case study | Expert Voice"
  description="How LuminNote built a TikTok presence from zero to 819K views in 60 days, with data-led content iteration and a coordinated email playbook."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="case-study-page">
    <header class="case-hero">
      <div class="container case-hero-inner">
        <a href="/#cases" class="case-back">← All case studies</a>
        <div class="case-eyebrow">Case study · AI Platform</div>
        <h1 class="display">LuminNote</h1>
        <p class="case-subtitle">From zero TikTok presence to nearly a million views in two months, with content built around real student pain points and a coordinated email playbook.</p>

        <div class="case-hero-stats">
          <div class="case-hero-stat">
            <div class="case-hero-stat-num">819K</div>
            <div class="case-hero-stat-label">Views in 60 days</div>
            <div class="case-hero-stat-context">Almost a million people discovered LuminNote on TikTok in two months. All organic, no paid promotion.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="case-hero-stat">
            <div class="case-hero-stat-num">+1,067%</div>
            <div class="case-hero-stat-label">Month-on-month growth</div>
            <div class="case-hero-stat-context">Likes jumped from 5,707 in month one to 66,593 in month two as the formula clicked into place.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="case-hero-stat">
            <div class="case-hero-stat-num">72.3K</div>
            <div class="case-hero-stat-label">Total likes</div>
            <div class="case-hero-stat-context">Across the first 60 days. Comments asked "what's this app called?" on repeat.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="case-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="case-section-grid">
          <div class="case-section-label">Where they started</div>
          <div class="case-section-body">
            <p>LuminNote is an AI platform built for students. When we picked up the TikTok and email channels, there was no short-form video presence at all and no system in place to turn social attention into product sign-ups. TikTok and email became the only two growth channels — and the audience had to be built from a standing start.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-section case-section-tinted">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="case-section-grid">
          <div class="case-section-label">How we worked together</div>
          <div class="case-section-body">
            <div class="case-work-grid">
              <article class="case-work-card">
                <div class="case-work-num">01</div>
                <h3>TikTok built from zero</h3>
                <p>Channel created and managed from scratch. Content strategy, filming approach, hooks, captions and posting rhythm all built and run end-to-end.</p>
              </article>
              <article class="case-work-card">
                <div class="case-work-num">02</div>
                <h3>Student-first content strategy</h3>
                <p>Every video leads with a relatable student pain point or academic struggle, then positions LuminNote as the solution in the first few seconds. Comments asking "what's the app called?" became the consistent signal that the format was working.</p>
              </article>
              <article class="case-work-card">
                <div class="case-work-num">03</div>
                <h3>Data-led monthly iteration</h3>
                <p>Month one set the baseline. Month two refined the formula based on what actually performed, and the best-performing formats were scaled up. That's how the channel went from 5,707 likes to 66,593 in 30 days.</p>
              </article>
              <article class="case-work-card">
                <div class="case-work-num">04</div>
                <h3>Coordinated email campaigns</h3>
                <p>Emails sent in sync with the videos that were performing — feature explainers and offers timed to the moments when audience attention was peaking on TikTok.</p>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="case-section-grid">
          <div class="case-section-label">The result</div>
          <div class="case-section-body">
            <div class="case-result-group">
              <h3>TikTok went from quiet to almost a million views</h3>
              <p>Across 60 days, the LuminNote TikTok pulled in over 800,000 views and 72,000+ likes. From a standing start. The audience grew at the same time, from zero to 334 followers, all of them students who were genuinely interested.</p>
              <div class="case-stat-row">
                <div class="case-stat-card">
                  <div class="case-stat-num">819K</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-label">Total views</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-context">60 days, organic only</div>
                </div>
                <div class="case-stat-card">
                  <div class="case-stat-num">72.3K</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-label">Total likes</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-context">Month 1: 5,707 → Month 2: 66,593</div>
                </div>
                <div class="case-stat-card">
                  <div class="case-stat-num">334</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-label">New followers</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-context">From zero in 60 days</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="case-result-group">
              <h3>Month two is where the algorithm clicked</h3>
              <p>The first month was the foundation. By month two, the highest-performing formats had been identified and the formula clicked. Likes grew more than eleven-fold in 30 days, and the top videos started hitting five-figure engagement on their own.</p>
              <div class="case-stat-row">
                <div class="case-stat-card">
                  <div class="case-stat-num">+1,067%</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-label">Month-on-month growth</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-context">In likes alone</div>
                </div>
                <div class="case-stat-card">
                  <div class="case-stat-num">14,600</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-label">Top video likes</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-context">Best-performing video</div>
                </div>
                <div class="case-stat-card">
                  <div class="case-stat-num">5</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-label">Videos above 4K likes</div>
                  <div class="case-stat-context">Not a one-off spike</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-section case-section-callout">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="case-callout">
          <h3>What this all means</h3>
          <p>TikTok isn't only an awareness channel for the right product. With content built around real student pain points and a coordinated email layer underneath, short-form video moves people from "scroll" to "what's this app called?" in seconds. The first month is the foundation. The second month is where compounding starts to do the heavy lifting.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-cta-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="display">Want this kind of reach for your product?</h2>
        <p>Book a 15-minute intro call. No pitch, just a clear read on whether we're a fit.</p>
        <a href="/#book" class="btn-primary">
          <span>Book a call</span>
          <svg class="arrow" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
